    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Destination Board Lights (Optional)</title>
        <para>The destination sign or board option includes a translucent glass panel on the exterior of the front and
            rear end caps. The illumination for these panel are from lights on the inside of the end cap assembly. These
            lights are accessed through the lift up door on the header assembly directly behind the destination board.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Open the access door and locate the destination board bulbs and sockets.</para>
            <figure id="f47006204" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg47/G47006204.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 204. Lighted Destination Board Bulb Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. BULB ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. DESTINATION SIGN (GLASS)</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. DRIVER OVERHEAD BULKHEAD</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. VISOR MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. VISOR</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the bulb or bulbs.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
